post_text:
Starting September 14th we will be offering free meals to all students. This includes one regular breakfast and one regular lunch daily at all sites. We will also start curbside meals on September 14th only at the high school in the U drive from 11:00 am-1:00npm daily for any person up to 18 years of age. Any student in Waseca who is a distance learner would be able to come to the high school U drive daily to pick up breakfast and lunch.

We plan to also open Hartley up as a curbside pick up on September 21st. More details will follow next week.

post_text:
Our School Board has a regular meeting Thursday, Aug. 20 at 5:30pm. The Waseca School Board invites the public to attend our meeting in-person or to watch the livestream on Facebook. We will also post a recording to our website. Meetings are held in the PAC and visitors should enter the building using door W17. All visitors must wear a mask and maintain social distancing of at least 6ft (roughly 2 chairs between each visitor). Visitors who wish to speak at the meeting should follow policy #206 and only speak during the public comment period on the agenda. Visitors watching from home can email their comments before 5:00 p.m. to wasecadistrict@gmail.com and the chair will read the email during the meeting. The School Board reserves the right to close the meeting if the number of in-person visitors exceeds safe social distancing requirements.

At tomorrow's meeting, the Board will be reviewing and approving the Base Learning Model to begin our school year.

post_text:
Parents and Guardians,

If you have not already done so, please access the Parent Portal to electronically update your child's information. All families must complete this step by the end of the day on Monday, August 17. It is extremely important that we have accurate contact information for your student. In addition, the Technology Responsible Use Agreement is included with this annual update. The agreement must be accepted in order to receive a device at applicable grade levels if you do not already have one, or prevent your current device from being deactivated. Further information can be found on the district website and your Parent Portal. Please contact the applicable school site if you need access to, or assistance with, the Parent Portal. We appreciate your assistance with this task.

post_text: FEC Families - check out this announcement!
shared_text:
Waseca Family Education Center
August 4 at 10:23 AM ·

Hello FEC families! We are excited to announce our plans for the Junior Jays preschool program to begin the 2020 school year. We will be able to keep children in class on the days/times they were originally scheduled to attend! The Waseca Public School District will be going back in a hybrid model and we are doing the same. We are able to keep our classes in small groups and/or in rooms that allow for us to be at 50% occupancy of the room, but children will still be able to attend school in person every day they are scheduled, with the same teachers each day. We are making changes to make sure to keep staff and students safe. Current families, please make sure to check your email for information and a short survey that was sent out on Monday. If you have any specific questions or concerns, please contact our office at 507-835-2222.

post_text:
We are very happy to post this press release:

Waseca Public Schools has completed the interview process for the Junior High/Senior High Principal position and are pleased to announce that Dr. Jason Miller has accepted this position. Dr. Miller has served as Assistant Principal at Waseca JSHS for the past 5 years and his previous experiences include serving as a teacher and instructional coach in Mankato Public Schools for 20 years. He also has served as an adjunct faculty member with Hamline University since 2008. He Has a bachelor’s degree from Bowling Green State University, a master’s degree from Minnesota State-Mankato, and earned his doctorate from St. Mary’s University.

Jason will begin his duties July 1, 2020, pending approval at the May 21 School Board meeting. He is replacing Jeanne Swanson, who is retiring at the end of June.

Congratulations to Dr. Miller on your new position!
text:
We are very happy to post this press release:

Waseca Public Schools has completed the interview process for the Junior High/Senior High Principal position and are pleased to announce that Dr. Jason Miller has accepted this position. Dr. Miller has served as Assistant Principal at Waseca JSHS for the past 5 years and his previous experiences include serving as a teacher and instructional coach in Mankato Public Schools for 20 years. He also has served as an adjunct faculty member with Hamline University since 2008. He Has a bachelor’s degree from Bowling Green State University, a master’s degree from Minnesota State-Mankato, and earned his doctorate from St. Mary’s University.

Jason will begin his duties July 1, 2020, pending approval at the May 21 School Board meeting. He is replacing Jeanne Swanson, who is retiring at the end of June.

Congratulations to Dr. Miller on your new position!

Registration for the 2020-21 school year is now open for students currently in grades 8-11. Everything is accessible through the students’ Counseling Course in Schoology, and information will also be on the Counseling website. Please watch the instructional videos before filling out the online registration form.

If you have any questions about registration, please contact your counselor or the office.

The following applies to 11th graders only:
Due to the Governor’s Stay at Home Order, the ACT will not be given on April 21st. We have been working with ACT on alternative options, and as soon as we have more details we will share the update. Please check the 11th grade Counseling Course in Schoology. We will also be able to give the Accuplacer at any time next year, and we can reschedule the ASVAB test for next fall.

post_text:
Did you see our stadium lights on this week? Starting April 1st, Waseca High School Joined The “Be the Light” Campaign.
Waseca High School announced that it will be joining the “Be the Light” campaign which started last week at Dumas High School in Texas. Since its first evening the Be the Light campaign has spread across Texas, Colorado, and our nation as “a symbol of hope and an assurance that you are in our hearts and minds” during such a difficult and trying time.
The stadium lights at the Waseca High School football stadium will be turned on for 15 minutes every weekday starting at 7:45pm and will remain on for 15 minutes until the end of the school year.
Schools across the state are being encouraged to share photos of their stadium lights on in a sign of solidarity and hope using the hashtag #BeTheLightM
We are all in this together and together, we can accomplish anything, Waseca! We’re here for you!

post_text:
The first day of Distance Learning went relatively well today. Schoology and See-Saw had some issues but they seemed to resolve. If you have questions or concerns about how things are working for your family, please contact your child’s school and/or teacher tomorrow. Please also familiarize yourselves with the Distance Learning Plan on our website if you have not already done so.

Today the Jays Nest cared for 31 children of emergency workers and food service served 1055 meals.

We have listed some additional resources on how to take care of yourselves and your family during Shelter in Place on our website.

That is it for tonight. Now that every essential school function is up and running, I will reduce the number of phone calls to your and only send something out if it is critical information. Thank you all for your patience and support. The WPS will do everything possible to make the most out of our shared new reality. Have a great night.

post_text:
WEM, Waseca seeded for girls basketball tourney
Chad Courrier, Mankato Free Press

MANKATO -- Waterville-Elysian-Morristown was seeded fourth in Class A and Waseca was seeded fifth in Class AA for next week's girls basketball state tournaments.

WEM (26-4), making the first state appearance in program history, will face Heritage Christian in the quarterfinal at 1 p.m. Thursday at University of Minnesota's Pavilion.

Other quarterfinal matchups are No. 1 Minneota vs. Red Lake, No. 2 Cromwell-Wright vs. Belgrade-Brooten-Elrosa and No. 3. Henning vs. Fillmore Central.

Waseca (24-6) will play Pelican Rapids in the quarterfinals at 8 p.m. Wednesday at Williams Arena.

Other quarterfinal matchups are No. 1 Rochester Lourdes vs. Concordia Academy, No. 2 Sauk Centre vs. Providence Academy and No. 3 New London-Spicer vs. Duluth Marshall.

The Free Press

post_text: This is such a good day - Waseca can share in these contributions to making it even better with our Jays involved!
shared_text:
John Diedrich is with Michel Fritz Sorenson and 13 others.
February 22 at 1:05 PM ·

2.22.2020 Arik Matson Day in Waseca- It seems appropriate to make this announcement today.
The online auction of the Waseca Boys Hockey Jerseys to benefit officer Matson will be held April 1st -5th 2020

Each one of the Varsity Boys jerseys will be available – all proceeds from the successful donators / bidders will be processed through the Waseca Hockey Association 501c3 making them 100% tax deductible.
Each one of a kind, Arik Matson- Waseca Police Jersey was designed & crafted for the Waseca Blue Jays Hockey Teams and donated by Chris Bonvino of Gemini Athletic. These Jerseys played an inspirational role in the record breaking 18-9 season for the Waseca Blue Jays and will now be offered at auction with all proceeds going to the family of officer Arik Matson.
Officer Mason has helped make a difference in our lives now it’s our turn to step up and return the favor. Let’s bid often and enthusiastically and take care of those who have taken care of us!

Please Share.

Waseca Junior/Senior High School PTO
January 22 at 10:01 AM ·

Good morning everyone on this crazy weather day!
The JH/SH PTO is hoping for your help.
At every trimester parent/teacher conference time, the PTO organizes an after school meal for all of the staff.
We are in need of a few things for tomorrow’s conference, so that we have enough food for everyone. (We are serving pulled pork sandwiches on a bun)
We are asking for 4 salads and 3 more desserts.
So if we can get 7 people to volunteer to each bring 1 of these things we will be set.
They will eat right after school so if you can deliver by 2:30 tomorrow that would be awesome.
We appreciate everyone’s help, and if you have any questions please feel free to contact me.
If you can help out please let us know so we have an idea of what is being provided.
Thank you very much!

Gretchen Sankovitz
PTO president

post_text: Today, there was a note left on a bathroom stall at the JSHS with a specific threat against the JSHS. Students there dismissed at 12:24 and the building was evacuated. Those students who drove to school were instructed to go home. All other students were evacuated to the Central Building auditorium. Because the threat was specifically against the JSHS, it was decided to continue school in the rest of the district. If you have a student who has been evacuated to Central and wish to pick them up, please come into the main entrance by the flagpole. Students who do not reunify with a family member will either wait until their ride arrives or they will go home on the buses at the end of the day.

post_text:
As you probably know, last night there was an officer involved shooting here in Waseca. Officer Arik Matson was airlifted to North Memorial Hospital where he is in critical condition. Our thoughts and prayers are with Officer Matson, his family and all law enforcement. You may not be aware that Officer Matson has been our DARE Officer the last several years and has had sustained contact with our students in this role. Many of our students know him well. Whenever something like this happens, kids respond in a variety of ways. We wanted to post this link to help guide you in any potential conversations that may come up in the next few hours/days. We believe it offers sound advice. Counselors are and will be available at school to assist any student necessary. We want to offer as much support to our students and families as needed. Please continue to keep Officer Matson in your thoughts and prayers!

http://bit.ly/36xNXBb

Need a great gift for someone or even for yourself? Jesters Comedy Improv is coming to Waseca!!

In the same vein as the hit television show "Whose Line Is It Anyway?", Jesters Comedy Improv features a hilarious troupe of off-the-cuff performers who’ll do just about anything for a good laugh. This fast-paced, game-oriented comedy performance will keep you on your toes and in stitches as these Grade-A comedians bounce from topic-to-topic with ease, creating comedic scenes, hilarious songs, and original jokes, all built off of suggestions from the audience and volunteers.

WHEN: Saturday, January 11, 2020
7:00 pm

WHERE: Waseca High School Performing Arts Center

WHAT: $10 – General Seating Tickets

Tickets are available at the Waseca Community Education Office (cash, check, credit card), or at the door the night of the event (cash and check only).

Don't miss this one-of-a-kind event held in our beautiful new PAC just after the holidays!

post_text: Last evening two BB guns and BB's were found in a baseball dugout behind the Jr. & Sr. High School Building. An investigation took place immediately this morning which included our School Resource Officer. We identified the students involved and appropriate action took place. Based on the facts of the investigation by law enforcement and administration, at no time was there ever intent to harm any students or enter any school building. We appreciate the individual who discovered and brought them to our attention. It is reassuring to know that individuals in our community are looking out for the safety of our kids.
